{"TopicId":188746,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Finding surface features","CreatedByName":"Capt. Hunt","CreatedById":97860,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-08T07:45:07Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Capt. Hunt","CreatedById":97860,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-08T07:45:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a trick to finding the new surface features?\u00A0 I\u0027ve been driving around the mun for hours looking for Mun Large Crater to complete a contract, but I have yet to see one.\u00A0 I\u0027ve seen a few Mun Stones and a couple of the smaller Mun Craters, but no large craters.\u00A0 It doesn\u0027t help that the features seem to blend into the background from any distance over a couple hundred meters.\u00A0 Is there something I\u0027m missing?\u00A0 Anything that might improve my chances of finding one?\u00A0 Someone on Reddit suggested making a low orbital pass over my landing zone, but it seems like that would run into the same problems that I\u0027m having driving on the surface, plus the added hassle of only having seconds to spot potential targets before my craft passes over the horizon.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-10-08T07:47:20Z\u0022 title=\u002210/08/2019 07:47  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 8, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Capt. Hunt\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-08T08:30:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen you open the debug menu (ALT F12), under Breaking Ground - Surface Features, there\u0027s a check box Surface Feature Finder\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-08T08:38:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the contract it says where you\u0027re likely to find them. Make sure you\u0027re in one of those biomes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWait until evening/morning so shadows are longer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTurn off ground scatter in the settings, so the only \u0022scatter\u0022 on the ground will be those anomalies.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd if that fails, do what \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/196199-voidsquid/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022196199\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/196199-voidsquid/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@VoidSquid\u003C/a\u003E said.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AHHans","CreatedById":197939,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-08T09:32:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223683436\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188746\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221570520707\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297860\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Capt. Hunt\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Capt. Hunt said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomeone on Reddit suggested making a low orbital pass over my landing zone,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think that will work. I have the feeling that the surface features are only rendered once you are fairly close and didn\u0027t zoom out too much. So you\u0027d have to get so close that the ground just speeds across your field-of-view.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy guess is that your problem is the first one on \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/73725-5thhorseman/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002273725\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/73725-5thhorseman/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@5thHorseman\u003C/a\u003E\u0027s list: there just aren\u0027t any in the biome you are looking. (Well \u003Cu\u003Eguess\u003C/u\u003E!)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-10-08T09:34:12Z\u0022 title=\u002210/08/2019 09:34  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 8, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by AHHans\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-08T10:00:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso: you have the BG surface features enabled? If you\u0027re not sure, check your persistent.sfs file, it should have a line reading\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nROCSeed = \u0026lt;somerandomnumber\u0026gt;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you are continuing an old game you started before BG, that line will be missing, hence no BG surface features will be present.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AHHans","CreatedById":197939,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-08T10:23:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223683489\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188746\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221570528806\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196199\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidSquid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 minutes ago, VoidSquid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso: you have the BG surface features enabled?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, it would have been pretty hard for \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/97860-capt-hunt/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002297860\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/97860-capt-hunt/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Capt. Hunt\u003C/a\u003E to find Mun Stones and Small Craters if he hadn\u0027t. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-08T13:00:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMurphy\u0027s Law \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Capt. Hunt","CreatedById":97860,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-08T19:19:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223683500\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188746\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221570530201\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022197939\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AHHans\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, AHHans said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, it would have been pretty hard for \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/97860-capt-hunt/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002297860\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/97860-capt-hunt/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Capt. Hunt\u003C/a\u003E to find Mun Stones and Small Craters if he hadn\u0027t. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nlol, yes they are enabled, and I started a new game when BG came out.\u00A0 I am also in NW Crater, one of the biomes suggested by the contract, although the wiki does say the mun large crater can spawn anywhere on the mun.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223683452\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188746\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221570523432\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196199\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidSquid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, VoidSquid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen you open the debug menu (ALT F12), under Breaking Ground - Surface Features, there\u0027s a check box Surface Feature Finder\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll look for that.\u00A0 How is this Surface Feature Finder supposed to work?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AHHans","CreatedById":197939,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-08T19:22:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223683726\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188746\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221570562347\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297860\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Capt. Hunt\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Capt. Hunt said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow is this Surface Feature Finder supposed to work?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a red \u0022arrow\u0022 like they are used to show the aero forces when that is active. But I suggest that you activate it while being close to a Surface Feature that you already found and look for yourself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Capt. Hunt","CreatedById":97860,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-09T01:55:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223683729\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188746\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221570562555\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022197939\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AHHans\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, AHHans said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a red \u0022arrow\u0022 like they are used to show the aero forces when that is active. But I suggest that you activate it while being close to a Surface Feature that you already found and look for yourself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nok, that does help make them way more visible, still haven\u0027t been able to find a large crater though.\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}